QUANTUM VIPER – ACCEPTABLE USE, SECURITY & SERVICE LEVEL AGREEMENT (UNIFIED POLICY)
Issued by: Morning Bay Technology Private Limited

1. PURPOSE
This Unified Policy governs the acceptable use, security framework, and service commitments of Quantum Viper (“Software” / “Services”). It forms an integral part of the Quantum Viper License Agreement.
By using the Software, the User agrees to comply with this Policy.

2. ACCEPTABLE USE POLICY (AUP)
2.1 Permitted Use
The Software may only be used for lawful purposes, including:
•	Code analysis and vulnerability detection
•	Software development and testing
•	Security research within legal boundaries

2.2 Prohibited Use
User shall NOT use the Software to:
(A) Illegal Activities
•	Violate any applicable law or regulation
•	Engage in fraud, cybercrime, or unauthorized access
(B) Harmful Conduct
•	Develop, distribute, or enhance malware, ransomware, or exploits
•	Conduct unauthorized penetration testing or scanning
•	Facilitate denial-of-service attacks
(C) Abuse of Platform
•	Interfere with system integrity or performance
•	Attempt unauthorized access to systems or data
•	Circumvent security or licensing mechanisms
(D) Competitive Misuse
•	Reverse engineer or replicate the Software
•	Build competing products using insights from the Software
(E) Data Misuse
•	Process data without proper authorization
•	Upload sensitive data in violation of law or contract

2.3 Enforcement
The Company reserves the right to:
•	Suspend or terminate access immediately
•	Investigate misuse
•	Report violations to authorities
No prior notice is required.

3. SECURITY POLICY
3.1 Security Philosophy
Quantum Viper follows a “best-effort, commercially reasonable security” model.
No system is guaranteed to be fully secure.

3.2 Infrastructure Security
The Company implements:
•	Access control mechanisms (role-based access where applicable)
•	Encryption in transit (where cloud/API is used)
•	Secure development practices
•	Monitoring and logging of system activity

3.3 Application Security
•	Regular updates and patches
•	Internal testing and validation
•	Secure coding practices
However:
•	The Software may contain vulnerabilities
•	The Company does not guarantee defect-free operation

3.4 Data Security
•	Local-first architecture where applicable
•	Optional cloud processing based on user configuration
User acknowledges:
•	Data security depends significantly on user environment
•	The Company is not responsible for user-side vulnerabilities

3.5 User Responsibilities
User must:
•	Secure their systems and credentials
•	Implement independent security reviews
•	Validate all outputs before use
•	Maintain backups of critical data

3.6 Incident Response
In case of a known security incident:
•	The Company will use reasonable efforts to notify affected Users
•	No guaranteed response or resolution timelines are provided

3.7 Vulnerability Disclosure
Users may report vulnerabilities to the Company.
By submitting:
•	User grants the Company rights to use and remediate
•	No compensation is guaranteed

3.8 No Security Warranty
The Company explicitly disclaims:
•	Any guarantee of security
•	Any obligation to prevent breaches
•	Any liability arising from security incidents

4. SERVICE LEVEL AGREEMENT (SLA)
4.1 Service Nature
Quantum Viper is provided on a best-effort basis.
No guaranteed uptime applies unless explicitly agreed in writing.

4.2 Availability
The Company does NOT guarantee:
•	Continuous availability
•	Error-free operation
•	Uninterrupted access
Downtime may occur due to:
•	Maintenance
•	Infrastructure failures
•	Third-party dependencies
•	Force majeure events

4.3 Support
Support (if applicable) is provided:
•	On a reasonable-effort basis
•	Without guaranteed response or resolution time

4.4 Updates & Changes
The Company may:
•	Modify or discontinue features
•	Release updates without notice
•	Change functionality at any time

4.5 No SLA Credits
User is NOT entitled to:
•	Refunds
•	Service credits
•	Compensation
for any downtime, performance issues, or failures.

